WEBVTT

00:11.272 --> 00:12.708
Hey.

00:12.795 --> 00:14.231
Sorry I'm late.

00:14.318 --> 00:16.799
It's no problem.
I had the chance to get a bun.

00:16.886 --> 00:18.148
Have you been practicing?

00:18.235 --> 00:19.976
I have.

00:20.063 --> 00:21.543
Tell me.

00:21.630 --> 00:27.766
<i>Elnézést, kaphatnék egy</i> <i>
kulonleges hamburgert?</i>

00:27.853 --> 00:29.420
Yes, very good.

00:29.507 --> 00:30.900
What does it mean?

00:30.987 --> 00:33.816
Excuse me, can I have
a special hamburger?

00:33.903 --> 00:36.166
You have been practicing.

00:36.253 --> 00:37.994
I've been
in Budapest long enough.

00:38.081 --> 00:40.953
I think a man needs to know how
to order a burger for himself.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.433
I agree.

00:42.520 --> 00:44.609
Look, I really appreciate
taking the time

00:44.696 --> 00:46.176
to teach me in the evenings, Sara.

00:48.396 --> 00:50.876
I tell you this honestly,

00:50.963 --> 00:54.663
I'd much rather be here
with you than go out dancing.

00:54.750 --> 00:56.795
You chose me over dancing?

00:58.710 --> 01:01.409
I guess I did.

01:01.496 --> 01:04.542
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:04.629 --> 01:08.198
Okay, uh, open your book
to the second section

01:08.285 --> 01:10.853
and we will learn new phrases.

01:15.510 --> 01:22.082
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:26.956 --> 01:29.437
- Guys, I gotta go to bed.
- Mm.

01:29.524 --> 01:31.526
Oh, I'm sorry
the duck was so salty.

01:31.613 --> 01:33.615
It was delicious, Shannon.
Don't be silly.

01:33.702 --> 01:35.399
Yeah, it was great.
My ankles are a little swollen.

01:36.879 --> 01:38.010
Thank you.

01:38.098 --> 01:39.360
At least when we eat here,

01:39.447 --> 01:40.926
we know nobody spat
in anything, right?

01:41.013 --> 01:44.669
Ain't that the truth.

01:44.756 --> 01:47.890
Tonight was the first night
in a while that felt...

01:47.977 --> 01:50.110
- Normal?
- Yeah.

01:51.807 --> 01:53.330
Maybe by the time
this one arrives,

01:53.417 --> 01:55.637
all the weirdness around here
will settle.

01:55.724 --> 01:57.117
From your lips to God's ears.

01:57.204 --> 01:58.161
Hmm.

01:59.989 --> 02:01.904
All right, all right.

02:01.991 --> 02:03.732
- Good night.
- Good night

02:03.819 --> 02:05.212
Thank you so much again.
- Yes.

02:05.299 --> 02:07.083
- I'll see you tomorrow at 2:00?
- At 2:00, yes.

02:07.170 --> 02:08.258
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

02:08.345 --> 02:09.564
- Bye, Daniel.
- Get home safely.

02:09.651 --> 02:10.739
- It was good, all right?
- Good night.

02:10.826 --> 02:12.088
Call you tomorrow.

02:12.175 --> 02:13.089
- Good night, guys.
- See ya.

02:13.176 --> 02:15.352
- Sleep well.
- Bye.

02:20.662 --> 02:22.881
What time is it in Atlanta?

02:22.968 --> 02:25.449
Mm, minus six hours.

02:25.536 --> 02:27.190
Oh, I gotta call Craig about
moving some money

02:27.277 --> 02:29.758
from the 312 account to the-- <i></i>

02:31.455 --> 02:34.154
What was that?

02:34.241 --> 02:37.157
The wine tanks.

02:37.244 --> 02:39.550
No, Daniel, don't.
Let the police take care of it.

02:39.637 --> 02:41.596
Just stay--stay inside. <i></i>

02:41.683 --> 02:43.902
What are you gonna do?

02:43.989 --> 02:46.340
It's not worth it.

02:46.427 --> 02:47.428
Please, please.

02:47.515 --> 02:54.435
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:02.660 --> 03:04.749
Hey!

03:04.836 --> 03:06.882
Enough!

03:06.969 --> 03:07.883
Do you hear me?

03:07.970 --> 03:14.716
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:14.803 --> 03:16.544
We told you,
we don't want troub--

03:19.808 --> 03:21.766
Daniel!

03:21.853 --> 03:25.030
No! No!

03:25.117 --> 03:27.163
Oh, God, oh, God.

03:29.383 --> 03:31.646
Just stay with me.

03:34.344 --> 03:37.739
Baby, oh, God.
Oh, God, oh, God.

03:37.826 --> 03:39.741
Oh, no.

03:42.874 --> 03:51.970
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:55.017 --> 04:02.503
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:02.590 --> 04:04.156
Morning.

04:04.244 --> 04:06.463
Europol's requesting
the FBI's assistance on a case.

04:06.550 --> 04:08.073
Jaeger's here.
- Lay down.

04:09.901 --> 04:11.163
Hey.

04:11.251 --> 04:13.514
An American man,
Daniel Spencer, 35,

04:13.601 --> 04:15.864
was shot and killed
on his vineyard eight hours ago

04:15.951 --> 04:17.082
in Occitanie, France.

04:17.169 --> 04:19.215
He is survived
by a wife, Shannon,

04:19.302 --> 04:21.609
and a baby he'll never see.

04:21.696 --> 04:23.785
What's the story
on the other couple?

04:23.872 --> 04:26.483
Amanda and Henry Martin,
business partners.

04:26.570 --> 04:28.964
Plus the two husbands went
to university together.

04:29.051 --> 04:30.879
- Suspects?
- No criminal records.

04:30.966 --> 04:32.837
By all accounts, inseparable.

04:32.924 --> 04:35.231
No offense, Jaeger,
but why is this more than

04:35.318 --> 04:37.407
a local homicide?
- The vineyard is located

04:37.494 --> 04:39.061
in an area known
to be inhabited

04:39.148 --> 04:40.932
by a civil protest group
named CRAV.

04:41.019 --> 04:43.239
Yeah, I know them, they're
on the terrorism watch list.

04:43.326 --> 04:45.285
Apparently Qaddafi once tried
to recruit them

04:45.372 --> 04:46.982
to overthrow
the French government.

04:47.069 --> 04:48.723
They declined, but still.

04:48.810 --> 04:50.202
They're known
for very aggressive,

04:50.290 --> 04:52.466
sometimes violent,
intimidation techniques.

04:52.553 --> 04:54.032
In other words, we're not
sure if this man's murder

04:54.119 --> 04:55.556
is a personal grudge

04:55.643 --> 04:57.558
or the start
of a terror campaign.

04:57.645 --> 04:59.516
- Precisely.
- It's good enough for me.

04:59.603 --> 05:00.909
Let's head to France then,
shall we?

05:00.996 --> 05:02.389
Yep.

05:02.476 --> 05:08.917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:18.318 --> 05:20.015
I've seen
"Under the Tuscan Sun."

05:20.102 --> 05:21.712
We're a long way from that.

05:21.799 --> 05:23.758
Yeah, I don't know anybody's
gonna be honeymooning here

05:23.845 --> 05:25.368
anytime soon.

05:25.455 --> 05:26.195
I commandeered
this empty store

05:26.282 --> 05:27.588
for us to work out of.

05:27.675 --> 05:29.198
Great.

05:29.285 --> 05:31.200
Raines, paper the windows
and start gathering background

05:31.287 --> 05:32.506
on persons of interest.

05:32.593 --> 05:33.985
The rest of us have interviews.

05:34.072 --> 05:40.949
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:52.917 --> 05:54.615
Even if there were footprints,

05:54.702 --> 05:56.921
the wine would've
washed them away.

05:57.008 --> 05:59.097
Here's the security footage
of the shooting last night.

05:59.184 --> 06:01.230
Now it's dimly lit
and there's a slight spin

06:01.317 --> 06:03.188
as he goes down,
but French forensics says

06:03.275 --> 06:05.321
that the shot likely came
from that direction.

06:07.062 --> 06:09.325
Yeah, that's a good
vantage point for a sniper.

06:11.545 --> 06:14.286
Bonjour, Detective LeGrand,
Detective Dupuis.

06:14.374 --> 06:15.549
- Scott Forrester.
- Bonjour.

06:15.636 --> 06:17.202
This is Special Agent
Cameron Vo.

06:17.289 --> 06:18.421
Hi, nice to meet you.

06:18.508 --> 06:19.683
Were you the first two
on scene?

06:19.770 --> 06:21.250
Yes, we were.

06:21.337 --> 06:22.817
Do we know where
the shooter took position?

06:22.904 --> 06:25.036
Not as of yet.

06:25.123 --> 06:26.386
Okay, I can get
a forensics team here to help

06:26.473 --> 06:27.952
unless you think
you got it handled.

06:28.039 --> 06:29.258
We have it handled.

06:30.694 --> 06:32.392
What can you tell us
about CRAV?

06:34.481 --> 06:37.701
You assume
this is their organization?

06:37.788 --> 06:39.268
I'm open to any theories
at this point.

06:39.355 --> 06:42.140
Well, uh,
CRAV are sometimes misguided,

06:42.227 --> 06:44.839
but their hearts are
in the right place.

06:44.926 --> 06:47.755
Outsiders call them terrorists
because CRAV stand up

06:47.842 --> 06:49.539
for themselves.

06:49.626 --> 06:51.498
Maybe a bit too vigorously
at times, but--

06:51.585 --> 06:52.934
Define vigorously.

06:53.021 --> 06:54.370
Please understand,

06:54.457 --> 06:57.155
the farmers in this area
have been humiliated.

06:57.242 --> 06:58.940
And I watched
the French government

06:59.027 --> 07:01.725
destroy them with uprooting.

07:01.812 --> 07:05.947
They forced them to pull vines
out by the root,

07:06.034 --> 07:09.167
forbid them from growing
a percentage of their land.

07:09.254 --> 07:12.693
"The prices will go up
from this," they promised.

07:12.780 --> 07:14.129
But it never happened.

07:14.216 --> 07:16.958
So now the growers have
less grapes to sell

07:17.045 --> 07:18.438
and more and more debt.

07:18.525 --> 07:20.701
And the people were angry
about that.

07:20.788 --> 07:22.529
Well, like I said, humiliated.

07:22.616 --> 07:24.661
You know, they have been forced
to sell to foreigners

07:24.748 --> 07:26.446
who have no respect
for the land,

07:26.533 --> 07:27.316
no respect for the people.

07:27.403 --> 07:29.187
Angry and humiliated.

07:29.274 --> 07:31.146
I mean, some might call
that a lethal combination.

07:31.233 --> 07:33.235
I suppose this is true.

07:33.322 --> 07:34.584
Do you think there's anyone
at CRAV

07:34.671 --> 07:36.020
who would be willing
to talk to us?

07:36.107 --> 07:37.544
You can try the co-op,

07:37.631 --> 07:40.242
though what reception
you will get,

07:40.329 --> 07:41.461
I cannot say.

07:41.548 --> 07:48.206
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:48.293 --> 07:49.730
Shannon,
do you mind telling me

07:49.817 --> 07:52.384
when you moved to France?

07:52.472 --> 07:56.432
Um, eight months ago.

07:56.519 --> 07:59.348
It was Daniel's dream
since he was a boy.

07:59.435 --> 08:02.830
And was it your dream too?

08:02.917 --> 08:06.355
He showed me this documentary
on the Provence region.

08:06.442 --> 08:09.314
I was all the way in.

08:09.401 --> 08:11.969
Vineyards were so gorgeous.

08:14.450 --> 08:17.758
Daniel had family money
and his job moved online,

08:17.845 --> 08:19.977
so we thought...

08:20.064 --> 08:23.241
if we don't do this now,
we'll always regret it.

08:24.808 --> 08:27.724
They even convinced us
to join them.

08:27.811 --> 08:29.465
Did you have family money
too?

08:29.552 --> 08:32.163
We were doing well enough.

08:32.250 --> 08:36.298
And Daniel was
Henry's best friend.

08:36.385 --> 08:37.604
I have to tell you,

08:37.691 --> 08:39.214
they didn't have
to twist our arms.

08:39.301 --> 08:40.868
We thought it was exciting.

08:42.478 --> 08:44.785
I had no idea that...

08:44.872 --> 08:48.310
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:48.397 --> 08:50.530
They hate us.

08:50.617 --> 08:53.141
They killed him
because they hate who we are

08:53.228 --> 08:54.403
that much.

08:54.490 --> 08:56.448
- Who hates you?
- The locals.

08:56.536 --> 08:59.016
They harass us constantly.

08:59.103 --> 09:00.540
How?

09:00.627 --> 09:02.193
It started
with spray painting

09:02.280 --> 09:04.152
and minor intimidation stuff,
you know,

09:04.239 --> 09:08.852
shouts on the streets,
dirty looks, dents in our cars.

09:08.939 --> 09:11.463
But then our front doors were
kicked in

09:11.551 --> 09:12.813
in the middle of the night.

09:12.900 --> 09:14.641
Did you ever feel like
what they were doing

09:14.728 --> 09:17.252
was coordinated, organized?

09:17.339 --> 09:19.254
It was escalating.

09:19.341 --> 09:21.169
Definitely.

09:25.303 --> 09:27.218
I'm sorry.

09:27.305 --> 09:34.617
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:34.704 --> 09:35.879
Daniel took the brunt of it

09:35.966 --> 09:37.881
'cause he was the face
of the winery.

09:37.968 --> 09:40.928
He's more gregarious
than I am by a mile.

09:41.015 --> 09:43.234
That's part of why I agreed
to go into business with him.

09:43.321 --> 09:45.759
Do you feel unsafe now?

09:45.846 --> 09:47.891
I'm asking because I can get
a car to sit out here and--

09:47.978 --> 09:49.197
You're not gonna be here forever.

09:49.284 --> 09:51.025
If they wanna attack again,
they're just gonna wait

09:51.112 --> 09:53.593
and come back when you're gone.

09:53.680 --> 09:56.291
How far do you live
from the Spencers?

09:56.378 --> 09:58.293
Three kilometers.

09:58.380 --> 10:00.034
The shooting happened
20 minutes after you left

10:00.121 --> 10:01.470
the Spencers' house.

10:01.557 --> 10:03.907
Did you see anyone on the road?

10:03.994 --> 10:06.170
Any strange cars or...?

10:06.257 --> 10:08.172
We saw a co-op truck
heading down the road

10:08.259 --> 10:10.000
in the direction of the winery.

10:10.087 --> 10:11.785
There's not a lot of traffic
around here at night,

10:11.872 --> 10:13.177
so I remember it.

10:13.264 --> 10:14.831
But I told the police.

10:14.918 --> 10:17.138
What they did
with that information...

10:19.531 --> 10:21.446
I--I gotta supervise a shipment
of wine.

10:21.533 --> 10:23.623
I understand.

10:23.710 --> 10:25.668
- I can stay.
- Call if you remember

10:25.755 --> 10:27.452
anything else
or if you see anyone

10:27.539 --> 10:29.150
on your property
who shouldn't be here.

10:29.237 --> 10:31.108
We wanna find out what happened
to Daniel Spencer,

10:31.195 --> 10:33.197
but we also wanna make sure it
doesn't happen again.

10:33.284 --> 10:36.897
Thank you, and we
so appreciate you being here.

10:36.984 --> 10:38.638
Like I said,
the French police can't

10:38.725 --> 10:41.118
or just don't wanna help us.

10:47.429 --> 10:54.610
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:54.697 --> 10:57.526
At Quantico, they taught us
this case file, Ken McElroy.

10:57.613 --> 10:59.615
Do you remember that name?

10:59.702 --> 11:01.573
No.

11:01.661 --> 11:03.837
Well, he was this town bully
in Missouri

11:03.924 --> 11:05.665
who kept harassing people,
and if they complained

11:05.752 --> 11:07.579
or reported him, he got worse.

11:07.667 --> 11:09.190
Child molestation charges,

11:09.277 --> 11:11.148
domestic violence,
I mean, the list goes on.

11:11.235 --> 11:13.847
He was just a universally hated
bad guy.

11:13.934 --> 11:16.414
So after years
and years of abuse,

11:16.501 --> 11:18.678
McElroy was gunned down
in broad daylight

11:18.765 --> 11:20.157
in the middle of town next
to his wife

11:20.244 --> 11:21.768
by at least two rifle shots.

11:21.855 --> 11:23.291
And the local police never
solved it.

11:23.378 --> 11:25.467
The whole town got together,
took care of McElroy,

11:25.554 --> 11:27.251
and kept their mouths shut afterwards.

11:27.338 --> 11:31.342
Except, by all accounts,
our victim is a good guy.

11:31.429 --> 11:35.956
True, but in both cases,
an entire town was fed up,

11:36.043 --> 11:38.785
pushed to its limits.

11:38.872 --> 11:40.003
What the hell?

11:40.090 --> 11:44.399
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:56.541 --> 11:57.978
Murder not enough for you?

11:58.065 --> 11:59.980
You're gonna pay for every drop
of this.

12:00.067 --> 12:01.982
- You seem upset, my friend.
- Upset?

12:02.069 --> 12:03.548
- We're trying to help.
- Help.

12:03.635 --> 12:05.463
You ran us off the road!

12:05.550 --> 12:07.204
That's ridiculous.

12:07.291 --> 12:08.815
Your driver turned too quickly.
- No, no, no.

12:08.902 --> 12:10.817
I know what happened here.
You did this!

12:10.904 --> 12:13.820
You are...

12:13.907 --> 12:15.430
Hey!

12:19.260 --> 12:22.045
- Hey, hey!
- Hey, hey, hey!

12:22.132 --> 12:23.525
Hey!

12:23.612 --> 12:25.483
Everyone, back!

12:27.268 --> 12:29.705
I'm with the U.S. Federal
Bureau of Investigation.

12:29.792 --> 12:34.231
I want everybody
to step back right now!

12:34.318 --> 12:36.407
FBI.

12:36.494 --> 12:38.061
And what gives you the right
to come to my country

12:38.148 --> 12:39.846
and pull out your guns?

12:39.933 --> 12:42.370
Look, we were here helping.

12:42.457 --> 12:43.719
The tanker was driving erratically

12:43.806 --> 12:45.590
and swerved off the road.

12:45.677 --> 12:46.983
We are grape farmers.

12:47.070 --> 12:49.377
It breaks our hearts
to see this.

12:49.464 --> 12:51.248
We're trying to help.

12:51.335 --> 12:53.947
Okay.

12:54.034 --> 12:56.819
Look, we're also gonna help
by collecting our friend here,

12:56.906 --> 12:58.386
and we will be on our way.

12:58.473 --> 13:05.306
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:39.253 --> 13:40.907
I understand you want
to speak with me.

13:40.994 --> 13:43.648
Olivier,
I'm the head of the co-op.

13:43.735 --> 13:45.694
I need to ask you about
your truck.

13:45.781 --> 13:47.435
We have dozens of trucks.

13:47.522 --> 13:49.785
One was spotted close
to the crime scene.

13:49.872 --> 13:51.308
The trucks have cameras.
No one would use one

13:51.395 --> 13:53.397
to commit murder.

13:53.484 --> 13:55.486
May I see the footage?

13:55.573 --> 13:58.620
<i>Oui.</i>

13:58.707 --> 14:00.230
My colleagues just came
from an overturned

14:00.317 --> 14:01.492
tanker truck of wine.

14:01.579 --> 14:02.711
Oh?

14:05.322 --> 14:07.063
Are you pretending
you didn't know it was going

14:07.150 --> 14:09.022
to be attacked or pretending
not to have heard yet?

14:12.329 --> 14:14.462
They imported Spanish juice.

14:14.549 --> 14:16.638
Slapped a label on it,
called it French, and sold it

14:16.725 --> 14:19.032
for a price that devalues
actual French wine.

14:19.119 --> 14:20.772
So you're saying the Spencers
and Martins

14:20.860 --> 14:23.079
sold fraudulent wine?
- Mm.

14:26.126 --> 14:28.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:28.128 --> 14:30.521
Do you know why our wine is
exceptional?

14:30.608 --> 14:33.437
It's generations of Frenchmen
waking up before dawn,

14:33.524 --> 14:36.397
spending their entire lives
studying every aspect

14:36.484 --> 14:39.791
of the soil, the crop,
the animals, the insects,

14:39.879 --> 14:41.054
all of it.
- And when novices come in

14:41.141 --> 14:43.795
and farm the same land,
that stings.

14:43.883 --> 14:45.797
Is there anything else
I can help you with?

14:45.885 --> 14:47.712
Because I don't get paid to ask
people questions for a living.

14:47.799 --> 14:48.888
I have to actually work.

14:50.628 --> 14:52.065
Who is this man?

14:52.152 --> 14:55.372
Hm, he's a hero.

14:55.459 --> 14:57.809
And I'm done speaking with you.
- Very well.

14:57.897 --> 15:00.290
But I need that footage,
s'il vous plaît.

15:00.377 --> 15:01.988
Sure, Madame.

15:05.992 --> 15:07.950
His name is Guillaume Marais.

15:08.037 --> 15:09.082
It seems like
a really poorly kept secret

15:09.169 --> 15:11.823
that he's the regional head
of CRAV.

15:11.911 --> 15:13.956
He was trained
in anti-insurgency tactics

15:14.043 --> 15:16.611
by the French Army
and brought those tactics home.

15:16.698 --> 15:19.222
For example, one family wanted
to switch from grapes

15:19.309 --> 15:20.702
to olive trees.

15:20.789 --> 15:23.183
Guillaume burned them down. Allegedly.

15:23.270 --> 15:24.619
The family replanted,
and those trees

15:24.706 --> 15:25.925
were also burned to the ground.

15:26.012 --> 15:27.230
Was he a sniper

15:27.317 --> 15:29.450
when he was with the army?
- Certified.

15:29.537 --> 15:30.973
And the local police still
haven't determined the position

15:31.060 --> 15:32.670
of the shooter,
casings, nothing?

15:32.757 --> 15:34.846
- Nope.
- CRAV actually got

15:34.934 --> 15:37.937
the terrorist designation after
they hit some deeper pockets.

15:38.024 --> 15:41.027
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:41.114 --> 15:43.159
But yeah,
they're brutal in their aim

15:43.246 --> 15:45.248
to keep things traditional.
- The cop at the crime scene

15:45.335 --> 15:46.858
told us the people here
are humiliated.

15:46.946 --> 15:47.816
I mean,
Guillaume stands up for them,

15:47.903 --> 15:50.123
makes those in power pay.

15:50.210 --> 15:53.169
A local hero
like what the co-op said.

15:53.256 --> 15:54.605
I reviewed the footage
from their truck

15:54.692 --> 15:55.824
that was on the road
last night.

15:55.911 --> 15:58.305
And Cameron,
if you'd be so kind.

15:58.392 --> 16:00.307
This is from the exact time
of the shooting.

16:00.394 --> 16:01.699
The driver was in his truck

16:01.786 --> 16:03.919
and the Martins were
in their car headed home.

16:07.575 --> 16:09.751
Has CRAV ever been linked
with any murders?

16:09.838 --> 16:11.448
No, I looked
into missing persons

16:11.535 --> 16:13.798
to see if they covered
something up, but no.

16:13.885 --> 16:15.496
So what is it
about Daniel Spencer

16:15.583 --> 16:17.106
that made them cross the line?
They've been using

16:17.193 --> 16:19.717
mafia-style
intimidation tactics for years.

16:19.804 --> 16:22.111
Why start killing now?

16:22.198 --> 16:24.287
I think the us-vs-them
situation here

16:24.374 --> 16:27.160
was a powder keg waiting
for the right match.

16:27.247 --> 16:30.946
Enter two American couples
with no experience in farming,

16:31.033 --> 16:35.081
plunking down cash
for their vineyards.

16:35.168 --> 16:37.822
We need to find someone
who interacts with both sides.

16:37.909 --> 16:39.128
Someone who can fill
in the gaps on why

16:39.215 --> 16:41.739
Daniel Spencer and CRAV escalated

16:41.826 --> 16:43.785
from intimidation to murder.

16:43.872 --> 16:46.092
There's an American chef
by the name of Jeremy Sheridan

16:46.179 --> 16:47.093
with his own restaurant
in town.

16:47.180 --> 16:48.007
Michelin star.

16:48.094 --> 16:50.009
If he can't be of any help,

16:50.096 --> 16:51.793
at least we can get a good meal
out of it.

16:51.880 --> 16:56.102
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:02.456 --> 17:04.588
I worked all over France
doing <i>stages</i> for years

17:04.675 --> 17:06.329
before I opened my own place

17:06.416 --> 17:08.723
so I could understand
the culture.

17:08.810 --> 17:10.812
Daniel and Henry show up,
throwing money around, saying

17:10.899 --> 17:12.553
how they're gonna revolutionize
French wine-making.

17:12.640 --> 17:14.685
My grandpa used to call
that "All hat, no cattle."

17:14.772 --> 17:16.122
Sounds right.

17:16.209 --> 17:16.861
So they made their way
to the top

17:16.948 --> 17:19.168
of CRAV's enemy list?

17:19.255 --> 17:21.214
I don't know about that.
It's a pretty long list.

17:21.301 --> 17:22.650
I was there myself
until I proved

17:22.737 --> 17:24.521
that I wasn't
some fly-by-night.

17:24.608 --> 17:26.393
I think the Martins
and the Spencers could've

17:26.480 --> 17:28.656
got there, too,
if they'd have been patient.

17:28.743 --> 17:30.832
Which is why I suggested
they sit down

17:30.919 --> 17:33.052
and talk with Guillaume.

17:33.139 --> 17:34.836
Did they? Talk?

17:34.923 --> 17:36.272
Daniel did, yeah.

17:36.359 --> 17:39.101
Henry wasn't
a super social guy.

17:39.188 --> 17:41.060
He was motivated
to get the community

17:41.147 --> 17:44.411
to embrace his family
before his son arrived.

17:44.498 --> 17:46.195
Do you think you could
arrange a sit-down for us

17:46.282 --> 17:47.153
with Guillaume like you did
for Daniel?

17:47.240 --> 17:48.850
I'd rather not.

17:48.937 --> 17:52.158
I just got off
their naughty list.

17:52.245 --> 17:53.420
Do you think
Guillaume's involved?

17:53.507 --> 17:54.986
He has the training,
the network,

17:55.074 --> 17:56.597
and a beef with the victim, so...

17:59.252 --> 18:05.910
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:07.956 --> 18:09.131
Hey!

18:10.741 --> 18:12.134
This yours?

18:19.794 --> 18:25.974
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:01.009 --> 19:08.234
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:08.930 --> 19:10.714
He says Guillaume was gonna
pay anybody

19:10.801 --> 19:13.500
who knew any information
on the American police.

19:13.587 --> 19:14.892
But Nicolas.

19:14.979 --> 19:17.547
You gotta understand,
he's not a bad guy.

19:17.634 --> 19:18.679
He's just trying
to feed his family.

19:18.766 --> 19:20.159
Well, maybe you've been
living here too long.

19:20.246 --> 19:21.943
Anyone who tries
to slice me open,

19:22.030 --> 19:24.728
that's a bad guy.

19:24.815 --> 19:26.382
Don't worry.
Decent chance he'll be back

19:26.469 --> 19:29.429
before the dinner crowd arrives.

19:29.516 --> 19:31.213
I want Guillaume sitting
in front of me

19:31.300 --> 19:33.259
in the next 30 minutes
or my next call

19:33.346 --> 19:34.216
is to the National Gendarmerie.

19:34.303 --> 19:35.522
I'll get some Paris cops
out here

19:35.609 --> 19:37.088
to take over
your investigation.

19:37.176 --> 19:44.357
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:55.672 --> 19:57.370
Mm.

19:57.457 --> 19:59.763
I don't wanna play this game.

19:59.850 --> 20:02.766
This insider-outsider thing.

20:02.853 --> 20:04.028
I don't think it's doing
your village any good

20:04.115 --> 20:06.770
and it's not helping me solve
a murder, so here it is.

20:06.857 --> 20:10.557
Let's talk about
Daniel Spencer's little boy.

20:10.644 --> 20:11.862
Let's talk about how
his mother's gonna have

20:11.949 --> 20:13.821
to tell him one day how much
he was looking forward

20:13.908 --> 20:15.562
to being a daddy,

20:15.649 --> 20:18.434
until he got shot dead
in his backyard.

20:18.521 --> 20:21.220
CRAV had nothing to do
with it.

20:21.307 --> 20:22.960
But you have been
harassing them.

20:23.047 --> 20:25.180
Vandalizing their cars
and kicking their doors in

20:25.267 --> 20:26.573
in the middle of the night.

20:26.660 --> 20:28.314
Me, personally?

20:28.401 --> 20:31.926
No.
- You attacked a shipment.

20:32.013 --> 20:34.320
You put a bounty out

20:34.407 --> 20:36.365
to interfere
with my investigation.

20:36.452 --> 20:38.585
I know these things, personally.

20:38.672 --> 20:40.108
Maybe.

20:40.195 --> 20:42.284
Maybe not.

20:46.375 --> 20:48.464
Do you see a pattern here,
Guillaume?

20:51.641 --> 20:54.775
Any sympathy
that the growers may have had

20:54.862 --> 20:57.430
with the French people
is gonna dry up.

20:57.517 --> 20:59.519
Uprooting, corporate interests,

20:59.606 --> 21:01.477
no one's gonna listen
to that anymore,

21:01.564 --> 21:03.914
because there's
a louder story now.

21:04.001 --> 21:05.525
So this is the part
where you threaten me

21:05.612 --> 21:07.135
if I don't tell you
what I know?

21:10.921 --> 21:12.183
No threats.

21:15.665 --> 21:17.798
Can I vouch for the actions
of every man in CRAV?

21:17.885 --> 21:21.410
No, that I can't.

21:21.497 --> 21:24.326
But no one would resort
to murder.

21:24.413 --> 21:27.198
And what makes you so sure?

21:27.286 --> 21:30.027
Because what I say goes.

21:30.114 --> 21:35.946
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:41.038 --> 21:44.259
<i>Merci.</i>

21:44.346 --> 21:46.261
The shooter
was positioned here.

21:49.482 --> 21:52.093
- .30-06.
- Yes.

21:52.180 --> 21:53.486
And there is also this.

21:55.531 --> 21:57.577
That typical of them?

21:57.664 --> 21:59.143
Leaving a calling card
like this?

21:59.230 --> 22:03.147
No, but there have been a lot
of firsts with this case, so...

22:03.234 --> 22:10.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:16.160 --> 22:18.119
Okay.

22:18.206 --> 22:19.642
That was Shannon Spencer.

22:19.729 --> 22:21.862
She wants someone to watch
over her while she packs.

22:21.949 --> 22:23.690
Go.

22:23.777 --> 22:28.347
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:28.434 --> 22:30.044
So we need a confession
from Guillaume

22:30.131 --> 22:31.524
or an eyewitness.

22:31.611 --> 22:32.568
The first one's
not gonna happen.

22:32.655 --> 22:34.265
The second one
is our only shot.

22:34.353 --> 22:35.658
I just got record back

22:35.745 --> 22:36.833
from Henry Martin's cell phone
and Guillaume's.

22:36.920 --> 22:39.183
They both have
incoming and outgoing calls

22:39.270 --> 22:41.185
to this guy, Tristan Moreau.

22:41.272 --> 22:42.535
Why would Henry call Tristan?

22:42.622 --> 22:44.754
Tristan Moreau,
I know this guy.

22:44.841 --> 22:46.147
Yeah, he was close
with Guillaume.

22:46.234 --> 22:48.018
Member of CRAV.

22:48.105 --> 22:49.977
But he was a bit too radical,
and he was banished

22:50.064 --> 22:51.848
from the kingdom, as it were.

22:51.935 --> 22:55.678
He is a very,
very dangerous individual.

22:55.765 --> 22:58.420
Also trained
with the French Army.

22:58.507 --> 23:00.683
Also sniper certified.

23:00.770 --> 23:02.250
His calls with Guillaume were
about a month ago,

23:02.337 --> 23:05.732
but his calls with Henry were
as recently as two days ago,

23:05.819 --> 23:08.778
just hours before
Daniel was killed.

23:08.865 --> 23:11.346
Henry hired him to take out
his friend?

23:11.433 --> 23:14.697
Wow.

23:14.784 --> 23:16.395
All right, I just pinged
Tristan Moreau's phone.

23:16.482 --> 23:17.961
It's active. He's traveling.

23:18.048 --> 23:20.877
Headed for...

23:20.964 --> 23:22.270
the Spencers' winery.

23:22.357 --> 23:25.186
He's 100 meters away.

23:25.273 --> 23:26.796
That's where Jamie's going.

23:26.883 --> 23:33.499
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:46.860 --> 23:48.122
- Thank you for coming.
- Of course.

23:48.209 --> 23:49.166
Come on in.

23:52.343 --> 23:58.654
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:13.234 --> 24:16.063
I just wanted someone
to be here while I pack up.

24:16.150 --> 24:18.152
I understand.

24:18.239 --> 24:20.197
Where are the Martins?

24:20.284 --> 24:21.242
At their house.

24:23.113 --> 24:25.115
They offered, but...

24:25.202 --> 24:27.335
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:27.422 --> 24:28.467
I just needed to be alone.

24:31.165 --> 24:33.602
I don't know if in all
this I forgot to say,

24:33.689 --> 24:36.300
but I'm very sorry
for your loss.

24:36.387 --> 24:43.830
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:44.526 --> 24:45.788
Kellett.
- Are you at the Spencers'?

24:45.875 --> 24:47.268
<i>- Yeah.</i>
- Who else is there?

24:47.355 --> 24:48.965
Shannon.

24:49.052 --> 24:50.358
<i>Get her and get out</i> <i>
of there.</i>

24:50.445 --> 24:52.491
- What's going on?
- There's a suspect nearby.

24:52.578 --> 24:54.667
<i>Just get her out of there.</i> <i>
We got two units on the way.</i>

24:54.754 --> 24:56.103
Is something wrong?

24:56.190 --> 24:58.888
You can pack later. <i></i>

24:58.975 --> 25:00.803
- Oh, my God.
- Do you have a safe room?

25:00.890 --> 25:02.892
- No.
- A room with a solid door

25:02.979 --> 25:04.503
and a deadbolt?
- The laundry room.

25:04.590 --> 25:06.069
Go there now and lock it.

25:09.159 --> 25:15.731
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:31.225 --> 25:37.971
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:40.930 --> 25:47.633
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:40.729 --> 26:42.862
He hasn't said a word.

26:50.783 --> 26:52.001
- Anything?
- Brick wall.

26:52.088 --> 26:53.307
We think Henry Martin hired
Tristan Moreau

26:53.394 --> 26:54.830
to off his friend.

26:54.917 --> 26:55.831
We're up
on Henry's phone now.

26:55.918 --> 26:56.876
He hasn't left
his ranch house.

26:56.963 --> 26:58.529
- Let's go snatch him up.
- No, no.

26:58.617 --> 26:59.966
Wait, wait, wait.
Just hold on one second.

27:00.053 --> 27:01.750
We've a very small window
to throw out some chum

27:01.837 --> 27:03.578
and see if we can get Henry
to bite.

27:03.665 --> 27:05.711
Prove he hired our hit man.

27:05.798 --> 27:07.277
Go get Tristan's cell phone.

27:07.364 --> 27:10.280
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:13.327 --> 27:16.112
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:16.199 --> 27:17.374
One sec.

27:21.335 --> 27:21.944
<i>Hé!</i>

27:24.904 --> 27:27.950
Pull up
Henry Martin's contact.

27:28.037 --> 27:30.344
- Got it.
- Any texts between the two?

27:30.431 --> 27:31.562
- Nope.
- Send one.

27:31.650 --> 27:33.260
10,000 euros
and I'll walk away.

27:33.347 --> 27:34.783
30 minutes.
Jeremy Sheridan's restaurant.

27:34.870 --> 27:37.046
What is that called?
- L'essence.

27:37.133 --> 27:39.309
Maybe this will lure
Henry out.

27:39.396 --> 27:40.833
- Sent.
- All right. You two, hit it.

27:45.489 --> 27:46.708
Hey.

27:49.363 --> 27:50.451
You sure you're okay?

27:50.538 --> 27:51.539
My mom always said
I had a rock

27:51.626 --> 27:52.583
for a noggin.

27:57.414 --> 28:04.595
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:09.513 --> 28:15.911
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:21.047 --> 28:23.484
Well, look who we have here.

28:23.571 --> 28:25.529
FBI.

28:25.616 --> 28:27.314
Okay.
What's going on?

28:27.401 --> 28:28.881
You tell us.

28:28.968 --> 28:31.405
I don't know.
I just got--

28:34.277 --> 28:37.933
I don't know what that's for.
I swear to God.

28:38.020 --> 28:39.805
I'm just supposed to give that
to someone.

28:39.892 --> 28:41.328
Let's go for a ride, Amanda.

28:41.415 --> 28:42.546
Wait, what?

28:42.633 --> 28:44.940
No. Wait. What's going on?

28:45.027 --> 28:46.942
Will someone tell me
what's going on?

28:47.029 --> 28:48.074
I didn't know what was
in there.

28:57.736 --> 29:01.087
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:01.174 --> 29:02.479
Take it.

29:09.356 --> 29:11.532
We have your wife in custody.

29:11.619 --> 29:13.273
Why?

29:13.360 --> 29:15.231
She tried to pay off Tristan,
but you know that.

29:15.318 --> 29:16.798
I do know that
because he's a psychopath

29:16.885 --> 29:18.234
<i>who's been shaking us down,</i>

29:18.321 --> 29:19.801
<i>and we wanted him</i> <i>
out of our lives.</i>

29:19.888 --> 29:21.498
<i>Why send your wife</i> <i>
to meet a psychopath?</i>

29:21.585 --> 29:22.456
<i>Because I was afraid of what</i> <i>
I would do to him</i>

29:22.543 --> 29:23.936
<i>if I saw him in person.</i>

29:24.023 --> 29:25.372
And it didn't occur to you
to mention Tristan

29:25.459 --> 29:27.853
to us earlier?
Seems like a glaring oversight.

29:27.940 --> 29:29.680
This is a man
who threatened to kill me

29:29.768 --> 29:31.291
if I spoke to the police
about CRAV.

29:31.378 --> 29:33.293
Clearly he's capable of murder.

29:33.380 --> 29:35.077
So yeah, I'm ashamed
I didn't tip you off,

29:35.164 --> 29:36.905
but I was hoping
that you'd find him,

29:36.992 --> 29:40.082
you'd arrest him, and wouldn't
involve Amanda and me.

29:40.169 --> 29:41.736
And before you judge me,
why don't you have a gun

29:41.823 --> 29:45.044
pointed in your face
and see how you'd react?

29:45.131 --> 29:47.655
So Tristan found you?
Wanted money?

29:47.742 --> 29:49.700
He was working for CRAV.

29:49.788 --> 29:51.964
They wanted the winery.
They wanted us out.

29:52.051 --> 29:54.967
Well, there's another theory, Henry.

29:55.054 --> 29:56.664
With the Spencers out
of the picture,

29:56.751 --> 29:58.318
you stood to benefit.

29:58.405 --> 30:00.320
There's some
very interesting language here

30:00.407 --> 30:02.191
about your partnership
with Daniel.

30:02.278 --> 30:03.845
If either one of you left
the winery

30:03.932 --> 30:05.934
and moved back to the U.S.,
the other would take over

30:06.021 --> 30:09.024
and pay the one who left
only the initial investment.

30:09.111 --> 30:11.810
The winery's worth 20 times
that now.

30:11.897 --> 30:16.205
So the money drop was payment
to a gun for hire.

30:16.292 --> 30:19.861
Daniel was my best friend.

30:19.948 --> 30:22.037
He and Shannon
were like family.

30:22.124 --> 30:25.345
And you're insinuating
that I'm behind this?

30:25.432 --> 30:28.217
It was CRAV.
They wanted us out.

30:28.304 --> 30:29.915
The harassment
has been documented,

30:30.002 --> 30:32.308
so are you blind
or are you just incompetent?

30:32.395 --> 30:33.788
And when we talk
to Shannon Spencer,

30:33.875 --> 30:35.050
she'll also know about Tristan?

30:35.137 --> 30:36.617
- No.
- Okay, what about your wife?

30:36.704 --> 30:37.966
She didn't know
about him either.

30:38.053 --> 30:39.402
The wives had nothing to do
with this.

30:39.489 --> 30:42.275
CRAV only came after
the husbands.

30:42.362 --> 30:44.973
Looking back now, I wish we had
gone to the police earlier,

30:45.060 --> 30:47.149
but who?
The local cops?

30:47.236 --> 30:48.455
We thought it would blow over

30:48.542 --> 30:50.239
if we showed CRAV
we had backbone.

30:50.326 --> 30:54.374
We never thought that
they would kill one of us.

30:54.461 --> 30:58.117
Still, I should've convinced
Daniel to involve you guys.

30:58.204 --> 31:00.510
Or leave.

31:02.556 --> 31:04.036
And that's a regret
I'll have to carry with me

31:04.123 --> 31:06.299
the rest of my life.

31:06.386 --> 31:11.652
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:11.739 --> 31:14.002
What do you think?

31:14.089 --> 31:16.439
I think there's one last drop
in the bottle.

31:16.526 --> 31:18.702
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:25.622 --> 31:27.015
<i>You ever play the game</i> <i>
musical chairs</i>

31:27.102 --> 31:28.756
<i>when you were younger?</i>

31:28.843 --> 31:31.672
<i>Eight kids walking in a circle</i> <i>
around seven chairs.</i>

31:31.759 --> 31:33.674
The music stops,
the kids scramble,

31:33.761 --> 31:36.764
seven kids get a seat,
and the one that didn't is out?

31:36.851 --> 31:39.419
Well, right now, today,

31:39.506 --> 31:42.117
there's one chair available.

31:42.204 --> 31:43.466
And your husband's
in the other room

31:43.553 --> 31:45.599
fumbling over his own words.

31:45.686 --> 31:47.253
<i>He just asked to take a break</i>

31:47.340 --> 31:49.646
so he could
gather his thoughts.

31:49.733 --> 31:53.346
Now I've been across a table
from guys like that 100 times.

31:53.433 --> 31:55.174
He will cave.

31:55.261 --> 31:57.480
Before lunch.

31:57.567 --> 32:00.570
So if you wanna tell us
what happened,

32:00.657 --> 32:02.529
you get the chair.

32:02.616 --> 32:05.662
And what comes with it
is consideration,

32:05.749 --> 32:08.665
a lesser sentence.

32:08.752 --> 32:10.929
But if you don't
wanna say anything,

32:11.016 --> 32:13.975
I'll walk down to Tristan,
offer it to him.

32:14.062 --> 32:17.283
And my guess is that
a self-serving career criminal

32:17.370 --> 32:20.982
like him knows how this works
and he will be actively trying

32:21.069 --> 32:24.768
<i>to save his own ass.</i>

32:26.945 --> 32:30.078
So I want you to think
about yourself.

32:30.165 --> 32:32.124
I want you to think
about your life

32:32.211 --> 32:34.778
and how you're gonna preserve
your hopes and dreams,

32:34.865 --> 32:36.998
because the music has
just stopped.

32:40.306 --> 32:43.396
Do you want the chair or not?

32:43.483 --> 32:49.837
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:50.925 --> 32:52.796
Okay.

32:58.019 --> 32:59.325
What's Henry said so far?

32:59.412 --> 33:01.327
That's not how this works.

33:04.460 --> 33:08.160
Henry knew about Tristan.

33:08.247 --> 33:09.683
Knew he was kicked out of CRAV.

33:12.251 --> 33:18.213
Henry's plan was to have
Tristan harass Daniel,

33:18.300 --> 33:19.910
to make them go back
to the U.S.

33:19.998 --> 33:23.610
and make it look like
CRAV was behind it.

33:23.697 --> 33:27.657
So the two of you could take
over the winery.

33:27.744 --> 33:30.008
Yes, but you have
to understand

33:30.095 --> 33:33.794
that when they came here,
they came as partners.

33:33.881 --> 33:36.231
Then Daniel
with his family money

33:36.318 --> 33:38.668
started treating Henry
like an employee.

33:41.019 --> 33:45.719
The plan--Henry's plan--
was just to scare them

33:45.806 --> 33:48.983
until they went back home.

33:49.070 --> 33:51.072
But even after the first
few things that Tristan did,

33:51.159 --> 33:55.685
like kicking in their door,
Daniel wouldn't leave.

33:55.772 --> 33:59.254
He was just too proud.

34:02.083 --> 34:03.563
Henry went to Tristan
to call it off,

34:03.650 --> 34:05.173
but Tristan refused.

34:05.260 --> 34:07.436
He wanted more money--
money we couldn't get

34:07.523 --> 34:10.831
unless we took over the winery.

34:10.918 --> 34:14.617
I mean, he threatened
our lives if he didn't get it.

34:14.704 --> 34:19.187
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:19.274 --> 34:20.710
The night of the shooting.

34:24.975 --> 34:27.587
Tristan was going to shoot
at the vats.

34:27.674 --> 34:30.677
That was it.

34:30.764 --> 34:33.201
I swear on my life,
Henry never agreed

34:33.288 --> 34:37.466
to have Tristan kill Daniel
in a million years.

34:41.470 --> 34:44.647
I am so sorry.

34:50.262 --> 34:57.095
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:06.626 --> 35:09.629
Henry will be charged
with second-degree murder

35:09.716 --> 35:11.500
since he set the whole thing
in motion.

35:11.587 --> 35:13.894
Amanda probably gets manslaughter,

35:13.981 --> 35:16.418
but since she's cooperated,
she'll get some rhythm

35:16.505 --> 35:20.422
and be sentenced to less time
in prison.

35:20.509 --> 35:22.903
I know this is a lot
to take in.

35:22.990 --> 35:26.515
On top of everything else
you've had to cope with.

35:26.602 --> 35:28.256
Your parents are landing soon,
right?

35:31.346 --> 35:35.568
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:35.655 --> 35:37.744
If there's anything you need
on my end,

35:37.831 --> 35:40.050
now or down the road,
you have my number.

35:40.138 --> 35:41.051
Thank you.

35:43.315 --> 35:45.404
For everything.

35:45.491 --> 35:46.883
Of course.

35:46.970 --> 35:52.019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:52.106 --> 35:55.240
I need to start putting
positive energy out there

35:55.327 --> 35:57.459
for my son.

35:57.546 --> 35:59.635
So I'm just gonna say this once

35:59.722 --> 36:01.071
and then leave it behind.

36:03.073 --> 36:05.337
I hope they both rot in hell.

36:05.424 --> 36:12.300
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:20.178 --> 36:22.441
This whole story,
it's very, very tragic.

36:22.528 --> 36:25.661
Money.
It's always about money, yeah?

36:25.748 --> 36:28.273
Family and love,
this is all that matters.

36:28.360 --> 36:29.578
Cheers to that.

36:29.665 --> 36:31.101
We hope your opinion
of Americans

36:31.189 --> 36:32.625
hasn't been tarnished.

36:32.712 --> 36:33.930
No, no. Not at all.

36:34.017 --> 36:35.758
No, you're welcome
back here anytime.

36:35.845 --> 36:37.717
Hopefully it won't be
in an official capacity.

36:37.804 --> 36:39.284
Very kind.

36:41.721 --> 36:45.768
Um, Guillaume is out front.

36:45.855 --> 36:48.336
He'd like a moment alone
with you.

36:51.383 --> 36:52.688
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:52.775 --> 36:53.994
You need backup?

36:55.952 --> 36:57.998
No, I got it.

36:58.085 --> 37:05.005
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:11.185 --> 37:13.318
You wanted to speak with me?

37:13.405 --> 37:14.667
You solved the case.

37:17.060 --> 37:19.193
Word travels fast.

37:19.280 --> 37:23.850
Well, when my organization
is exonerated,

37:23.937 --> 37:26.505
I like to be the first to know.

37:28.942 --> 37:29.943
Now...

37:32.293 --> 37:33.773
That's a great bottle of wine.

37:36.776 --> 37:39.518
It's local wine.

37:47.830 --> 37:49.179
<i>Adieu.</i>

37:49.267 --> 37:56.143
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:02.889 --> 38:04.586
If I ever say,
"Take me to wine country,"

38:04.673 --> 38:06.371
just go ahead and slap me.

38:06.458 --> 38:08.938
I will definitely not
be doing that.

38:09.025 --> 38:12.115
So much for keeping
your friends close, huh?

38:12.202 --> 38:15.031
Well, this is why
I don't have friends.

38:15.118 --> 38:17.860
Well, since we spent
all that time in France,

38:17.947 --> 38:20.254
what say we, uh,
crack this open

38:20.341 --> 38:21.690
and see what the fuss is about?

38:23.692 --> 38:25.564
Uh, I can't tonight, actually.

38:27.522 --> 38:28.610
I have something.

38:30.395 --> 38:32.310
Yeah. Of course.

38:35.138 --> 38:36.705
Rain check.

38:36.792 --> 38:39.055
Although I might need a bottle
of whiskey

38:39.142 --> 38:41.057
instead of a bottle of wine.

38:41.144 --> 38:43.930
Done.

38:44.017 --> 38:47.499
All right,
I will see you tomorrow.

38:47.586 --> 38:49.588
See you tomorrow.

38:52.678 --> 38:58.423
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:00.033 --> 39:02.601
Hey.

39:02.688 --> 39:04.080
I'm sorry I'm late again, Sara.

39:04.167 --> 39:05.691
I understand.

39:05.778 --> 39:07.214
No need to charge me
for the hour.

39:07.301 --> 39:09.129
I got some work done.

39:09.216 --> 39:11.653
Oh, but can't we just use
the rest of the hour?

39:11.740 --> 39:13.525
Scott,
I'm here to teach Hungarian,

39:13.612 --> 39:15.396
not manners.

39:15.483 --> 39:17.093
I apologized for being late.
I should've called.

39:17.180 --> 39:18.878
I just had a work thing.

39:18.965 --> 39:21.359
Your excuses mean nothing
to me.

39:21.446 --> 39:24.623
I quit and will no longer
be helping you.

39:24.710 --> 39:27.408
What? Really?

39:27.495 --> 39:29.802
- No.
- What?

39:29.889 --> 39:30.933
No, not really.

39:31.020 --> 39:33.501
Oh.

39:33.588 --> 39:35.590
You had me.
- I love working with you.

39:35.677 --> 39:38.680
Even if you az agyamra mész.

39:38.767 --> 39:40.987
What does that mean?

39:41.074 --> 39:42.771
Keep studying
and you'll find out.

39:42.858 --> 39:45.078
Uh, although since
we only have ten minutes left

39:45.165 --> 39:47.820
from our time,
we will have to move our class

39:47.907 --> 39:50.910
from this coffee shop
to a proper restaurant.

39:50.997 --> 39:52.477
Oh.

39:52.564 --> 39:54.392
Where you will be buying
me dinner.

39:54.479 --> 39:58.047
<i>Elnézést, kaphatnék egy</i> <i>
kulonleges hamburgert?</i>

39:58.134 --> 40:00.485
Oh.

40:00.572 --> 40:04.314
No, it will not be
a special hamburger.

40:04.402 --> 40:06.882
All right.

40:06.969 --> 40:08.318
I'm officially
turning my phone off.

40:08.406 --> 40:14.629
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:14.716 --> 40:16.283
You ready?

40:16.370 --> 40:17.371
As I'll ever be.

40:17.458 --> 40:24.639
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:36.564 --> 40:37.435
<i>Stay tuned for scenes</i> <i>
from our next episode.</i>

40:44.311 --> 40:50.926
<i>♪ ♪</i>
